text: Ha Chachole is a village in Malaoaneng community council, Leribe district, Lesotho. It is located at around , in the elevation of around 1962 metres.https://www.freemaptools.com/elevation-finder.htm ==Climate== Ha Chachole has a Subtropical highland climate (Cwb) with dry, cold winters and wet, warm summers. ==References== Category:Populated places in Leribe District
